{"TopicId":207928,"ForumId":15,"TopicTitle":"Recolor Mod that I\u0027m working on","CreatedByName":"Akagi","CreatedById":218751,"CreatedDateTime":"2022-04-26T14:25:08Z","PageNum":1,"Articles":[{"CreatedByName":"Akagi","CreatedById":218751,"CreatedDateTime":"2022-04-26T14:25:08Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThe other day, I thought up a good idea: recoloring stock heat shields. After a bit of drafting, I had a decent idea.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cu\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EHeat Shield Colors\u003C/strong\u003E\u003C/u\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cul\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\nRed\n\u003C/li\u003E\n\u003Cli\u003E\nBlack\n\u003C/li\u003E\n\u003Cli\u003E\nLight Gray\n\u003C/li\u003E\n\u003Cli\u003E\nGreen\n\u003C/li\u003E\n\u003Cli\u003E\nBlue\n\u003C/li\u003E\n\u003Cli\u003E\nOrange\n\u003C/li\u003E\n\u003C/ul\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\nWith some help from \u003Ca contenteditable=\u0022false\u0022 data-ipshover=\u0022\u0022 data-ipshover-target=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/220622-fleventeen/\u0026amp;do=hovercard\u0022 data-mentionid=\u0022220622\u0022 href=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/220622-fleventeen/\u0022 rel=\u0022\u0022\u003E@fleventeen\u003C/a\u003E\u00A0(thanks for finding GIMP), I will soon be releasing this!\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nCredits so far:\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Ca contenteditable=\u0022false\u0022 data-ipshover=\u0022\u0022 data-ipshover-target=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/66485-squad/\u0026amp;do=hovercard\u0022 data-mentionid=\u002266485\u0022 href=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/66485-squad/\u0022 rel=\u0022\u0022\u003E@SQUAD\u003C/a\u003E\u00A0Hmm... why exactly? Oh right, they made the 3D models, the game... everything!\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Ca contenteditable=\u0022false\u0022 data-ipshover=\u0022\u0022 data-ipshover-target=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/220622-fleventeen/\u0026amp;do=hovercard\u0022 data-mentionid=\u0022220622\u0022 href=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/220622-fleventeen/\u0022 rel=\u0022\u0022\u003E@fleventeen\u003C/a\u003E\u00A0for suggesting GIMP\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Ca contenteditable=\u0022false\u0022 data-ipshover=\u0022\u0022 data-ipshover-target=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/117203-manwith-noname/\u0026amp;do=hovercard\u0022 data-mentionid=\u0022117203\u0022 href=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/117203-manwith-noname/\u0022 rel=\u0022\u0022\u003E@Manwith Noname\u003C/a\u003E\u00A0for explaining how texture patching works\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nExpect a release sometime in the next month!\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nHowever, I did run into a problem: I have no idea how to use GIMP.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222022-04-26T14:25:52Z\u0022 title=\u002204/26/2022 02:25  PM\u0022 data-short=\u00222 yr\u0022\u003EApril 26, 2022\u003C/time\u003E by Akagi\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"ColdJ","CreatedById":211123,"CreatedDateTime":"2022-04-27T03:19:00Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00224122911\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022207928\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221650983108\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022218751\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Akagi\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n12 hours ago, Akagi said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nHowever, I did run into a problem: I have no idea how to use GIMP.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nTry Paint.net, it is easier. Remember that .dds are flipped upside down compared to .png Knowing where the UV maps of the part are on the texture pic makes life easier but will require something like blender with the .mu plugin to see where they are.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Ca href=\u0022https://www.getpaint.net/\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022\u003Ehttps://www.getpaint.net/\u003C/a\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nremember to set saving of .dds files to \u0022BC3 (linear, DXT5)\u0022 for them to work in game.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nVisit my thread that is right next door for info on the .mu plugin and for links to other helpful things.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"}]}